Bibliographic References: Kunst der Antike I (1978), no. 26, ill. on pp. 42Non Sepcified3.
Imagery Description: (a) Poseidon, with wreath and trident in right hand, fillet in left and Amyone, holding hydria in right, (b) A3v, with two eggs and fillet in left, stick in right, + A 2 r, with egg and stick.
Additional Notes: Neck: (a) siren, with 'skewer of fruit' and fillet in left, cista and wreath in right, (b) female head to left.
